until today,
one in Louisiana and Washington.
Describe

24:50.723 --> 24:51.690 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
those.

24:51.790 --> 24:53.425 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVE REITZE: So, these are two
interferometers.

24:53.525 --> 24:58.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Interferometer is a -- basically
a type of
laser measuring device. A laser
goes out.

24:58.931 --> 25:02.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It goes -- it gets split. It
goes along the
arms of the interferometers. And
they're very

25:03.035 --> 25:08.273 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
