long. Comes back. We do a lot of
tricks to

25:08.374 --> 25:10.175 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
make the interferometer very
sensitive.

25:10.275 --> 25:15.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And as a gravitational wave
passes, what it
does is, it stretches and
squeezes the light

25:15.914 --> 25:20.419 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
between the arms of the
interferometer. And
because light is made up of
waves, we use

25:20.519 --> 25:25.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the fact that that stretching
and squeezing
changes the relative
relationship, the phase,

25:26.091 --> 25:27.893 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
if you will, between the waves.

25:27.993 --> 25:30.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: So, do we --
how is it that
we got this sound? I mean, these
are lasers,

25:30.829 --> 25:32.664 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
